        conseils: "Walking along the Vauban ramparts is free and offers superb views of the Sambre and bastions. Maubeuge Zoo (€13) is set in the moats and bastions — original and pleasant, especially with children. For authentic Maroilles cheese, visit the Maison du Maroilles in the village of Maroilles itself (25 km south, the village that gave its name to the cheese): tasting, cellar visit and direct sales. Flamiche au Maroilles (warm cheese tart) is the Avesnois signature dish — try it in local estaminets. The Mormal Forest deserves a detour: 9,000 hectares of oaks and beeches with waymarked paths. Maubeuge's Italian-style theatre, rebuilt after 1945, is a small architectural gem. For beer lovers, Avesnois craft breweries (Bavaisienne, Épaulette) continue the northern brewing tradition.",
        comparaisonTransport: "The TER Lille — Maubeuge costs €15 and takes 1h to 1h15 with a change at Aulnoye-Aymeries. Frequency is modest (one train every 1-2 hours). By car, the route is entirely toll-free. The TaxiNeo taxi at €120 — €155 provides door-to-door service with no connections and crucially the option to visit the Avesnois (Maroilles, Mormal Forest, fortified villages) en route, which is impossible by train. For 3-4 passengers, the cost (€30-52 per person) is competitive against the train with its change.",
