          { question: "Does the taxi drop me at the cathedral?", answer: "Yes, your driver drops you at the Notre-Dame Cathedral forecourt, in the very heart of historic Amiens. Free drop-off, no parking worries." },
          { question: "Can we see the Chroma light show in the evening?", answer: "Yes, the Chroma light show illuminates the cathedral façade in summer (June-Sept, 10:30pm) and December. The taxi takes you back to Lille after the show." },
          { question: "Can the hortillonnages be visited year-round?", answer: "Boat tours run from April to October (€7, 45 min). The floating market takes place every Saturday morning in the Saint-Leu quarter, year-round." },
          { question: "How much is the Lille — Amiens toll?", answer: "The A1 + A29 tolls between Lille and Amiens amount to approximately €10, included in the TaxiNeo fixed price." },
          { question: "Can we visit Jules Verne's house?", answer: "Yes, the Jules Verne house-museum (2 Rue Charles-Dubois, €8) is a fascinating visit. Your driver drops you there. Allow 1 hour." }
