          { question: "Can we visit the La Tour pastel museum?", answer: "Yes, the Antoine Lécuyer Museum is open daily except Tuesdays. Entry: €5. It houses the world's largest collection of Quentin de La Tour's pastels." },
          { question: "Does the taxi drop me in the town centre?", answer: "Yes, your driver drops you at your chosen address: Place de l'Hôtel-de-Ville, station, hotel or any other point in the town centre." },
          { question: "Are there tolls on the route?", answer: "Yes, the A26 toll between Lille and Saint-Quentin is approximately €9, included in the TaxiNeo fixed price." },
          { question: "Is Saint-Quentin worth a full day visit?", answer: "Half a day covers the main sights (Art Deco, basilica, museum, marshes). A full day allows adding the WWI memorial sites in the Vermandois." }
