        routeDescription: "The route takes the A1 towards Paris then the A16 towards Beauvais, crossing the Artois and Picardy.",
        introduction: "Beauvais is a city of art and history in the Oise department, world-renowned for its Cathedral of Saint-Pierre, a masterpiece of Gothic architecture whose choir reaches 48.50 metres in vault height — the tallest ever built in the Middle Ages. This cathedral, left unfinished after the spire collapsed in 1573, fascinates by its boundless ambition and its 19th-century astronomical clock, a mechanical marvel of 90,000 parts. Beauvais is also famous for its National Tapestry Manufactory, founded in 1664 by Colbert, which perpetuates a centuries-old expertise in creating exceptional tapestries and carpets. The National Tapestry Gallery, facing the cathedral, displays remarkable pieces from the 17th to the 21st century. The city also boasts the Church of Saint-Etienne, blending Romanesque and Gothic styles, with exceptional Renaissance Tree of Jesse stained glass. Beauvais-Tille airport, the main Ryanair hub for the Paris region, serves over 60 European destinations and generates a constant flow of travellers needing reliable transfers. A taxi from Lille is particularly popular with passengers catching early morning flights or arriving late at night at Beauvais-Tille.",
        itineraire: "Your driver leaves Lille via the southern ring road and joins the A1 motorway towards Paris. After crossing the Pas-de-Calais mining basin with its characteristic slag heaps and red-brick terraced houses, you pass Arras and its baroque squares. The A1 continues through the vast cereal plains of the Artois and then Picardy. Near Roye-Mondidier, you leave the A1 to take the A16 towards Beauvais via Amiens-Sud. The A16 crosses the Picardy plateau, a landscape of large-scale farming and wooded valleys. You pass near Breteuil before arriving in Beauvais from the north. The Cathedral of Saint-Pierre signals itself from afar by its vertiginous height dominating the city rooftops. Combined A1 and A16 tolls amount to approximately 16 euros. The journey takes 2h10 normally and can reach 2h50 during weekend returns on the A1, particularly Sunday evenings between Arras and Lille.",
        conseils: "If catching a flight from Beauvais-Tille airport, plan to arrive at least 2h30 before take-off (check-in and security procedures are lengthy in this often-crowded terminal). Your driver drops you directly at the terminal. The Cathedral of Saint-Pierre is free to visit and the astronomical clock gives its demonstration at 10:40, 11:40, 14:40, 15:40 and 16:40 — do not miss this unique spectacle. The National Tapestry Gallery (free entry) deserves a 45-minute visit. The pedestrianised centre around Place Jeanne-Hachette is pleasant for lunch, with several traditional brasseries. The Beauvais market (Wednesday and Saturday) is renowned for Picardy local produce: regional cheeses, dulce de leche, and ficelle picarde. If you have time, Parc Saint-Paul (family theme park, 10 km away) or Troissereux Castle (5 km) make pleasant stops.",
        comparaisonTransport: "There is no direct train from Lille to Beauvais: you must travel via Paris or Amiens, with long connections (3h to 4h total, 30-60 euros). BlaBlaCar offers rides at 15-25 euros but with no schedule guarantee. By car, expect around 22 euros in fuel and 16 euros in tolls, totalling 38 euros excluding vehicle wear. The TaxiNeo taxi at 250 — 310 euros provides a direct door-to-door journey in 2h10, with no connections. For Beauvais-Tille airport transfers, it is the most reliable solution: drop-off directly at the terminal, ideal for early morning flights inaccessible by public transport. For 3-4 passengers, the cost of 63-103 euros per person remains reasonable for such a long journey with no direct alternative.",
        faq: [
          { question: "Does the taxi drop me at Beauvais-Tille airport?", answer: "Yes, your driver drops you directly at the Beauvais-Tille airport terminal, at the Departures or Arrivals entrance as needed." },
          { question: "How long is the Lille to Beauvais journey?", answer: "The journey takes approximately 2h10 via the A1 and A16 in normal conditions. Allow up to 2h50 during Sunday evening peak hours." },
          { question: "Can I visit the cathedral before my flight?", answer: "Yes, if your flight is in the afternoon. The cathedral is 10 minutes from the airport. Your driver can drop you there for a 30-45 min visit then take you to the terminal." },
          { question: "Are there tolls on the route?", answer: "Yes, combined A1 and A16 tolls amount to approximately 16 euros, included in the TaxiNeo fixed price." },
          { question: "Do you offer Beauvais to Lille transfers?", answer: "Yes, we provide Beauvais to Lille returns 24/7. Ideal for late-night flight arrivals at Beauvais-Tille." }
        ],
